sys.get_ip.description:
The **sys.get_ip** method returns a list of network interfaces as a dictionary. An example is available below:
```json
[
{
"name": "lo0",
"ip": "127.0.0.1"
},
{
"name": "lo0",
"ip": "::1"
},
{
"name": "en0",
"ip": "fd5f:a709:7357:f34d:c8f:9bc8:ba40:db15"
},
{
"name": "en0",
"ip": "10.0.124.42"
}
]
```
